    "created_at": "2014-06-04T18:30:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-04T18:30:40Z",
    "body": "Talking with others, it seems that the consensus for now is that this shouldn't be done as a codegen option, but rather enabled/disabled for particular triples. None of the currently supported triples should have segmented stacks disabled, so I'm going to close this for now.\n\nWe'd love to have more support for more triples, though! New triples supported in the compiler can opt-out of using split stacks on a case-by-case basis.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
